ğŸ“¤ Modules and Functions
1. Face Detection
Uses OpenCVâ€™s haarcascade_frontalface_default.xml to detect faces in webcam frames.

2. collect_faces()
Captures 30 grayscale face images from the webcam.

Resizes and equalizes each face image.

Saves them to dataset/<person_name>/.

3. train_model()
Reads all face images from dataset/.

Assigns numeric labels to each person.

Trains the LBPH face recognizer.

Saves the trained model to trainer.yml.

Saves label mappings to labels.txt.

4. recognize_faces()
Loads the trained recognizer and label map.

Captures webcam frames.

Detects and recognizes faces.

Displays the name and confidence level on screen.

ğŸ§  Model Used
LBPH (Local Binary Pattern Histogram)
Itâ€™s effective for small datasets and works well with different lighting conditions.

Parameters tuned:

radius=1

neighbors=8

grid_x=8, grid_y=8

threshold=100.0

ğŸ’» GUI Interface (Tkinter)
Widget	Purpose
Entry Field	Enter name before collecting faces
ğŸ“· Collect Face	Start face data collection
ğŸ” Recognize Face	Run face recognition live
ESC Key	Exit webcam window

ğŸ“ Usage Instructions
Run the app:

python main.py
